aplwrap is a GTK+-based wrapper for GNU APL.

Usage:
  aplwrap [OPTION...]

Help Options:
  -?, --help               Show help options
  --help-all               Show all help options
  --help-gtk               Show GTK+ Options

Application Options:
  -s, --ftsize             Font size in points [integer]
  -w, --width              Width in pixels [integer]
  -h, --height             Height in pixels [integer]
  -v, --vwidth             Use variable width font
  -n, --nocolour           Turn off coloured error text
  -x, --xeq                Path to the GNU APL executable [string]
  --LX                     APL startup command or expression [string]
  --display=DISPLAY        X display to use


aplwrap provides a textual interface to GNU APL. The window shows a
transcript of the APL session. New input to APL is always at the
bottom of the window; APL output and inputs that have been committed
to APL are uneditable.

The APL keyboard follows Dyalog APL conventions with a few changes.
View the keyboard layout using aplwrap's Help > Keymap menu.

See KEY_BINDINGS.md for details of keyboard interaction with the
transcript.

aplwrap command line options may be followed by -- and additional
options. These additional options are ignored by aplwrap. The entire
GNU APL command line is accessible to the APL program via the âŽ•ARG
system function.

aplwrap is tested using GNU APL 1.4 and later.


Contact me if I've screwed anything up or if there's a feature you
want added.

Have fun,
  Chris Moller
